Source: lorica-kernel-cloud
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Lorica Linux <lorica@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: lorica-kernel-cloud
Architecture: all
Depends: linux-image-6.12.74-lorica-lorica, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: lorica-lkrg
Description: Lorica Linux hardened cloud kernel (meta-package)
 Installs the Lorica hardened kernel built from kernel.org 6.12 LTS
 with full KSPP hardening, stripped for cloud server workloads.
 .
 This meta-package depends on the current Lorica kernel image.
 Install this package to track kernel updates automatically.
 .
 The kernel coexists with Debian's stock kernel. Select it via GRUB
 at boot time or set as default.
